Provides: niri
Description: A scrollable-tiling Wayland compositor (Devuan-optimized build)
 Niri is a scrollable-tiling Wayland compositor. Windows are arranged in
 columns on an infinite strip going to the right. Every monitor has its own
 separate window strip.
 .
 This package is compiled from the latest git source with optimizations
 for x86-64-v3 and built without systemd dependencies. It integrates with
 elogind/libseat for session management and supports dinit for session
 startup on Devuan.
 .
 For systems using sysvinit, openrc, or runit, the niri-session launcher
 automatically falls back to dbus-run-session for proper D-Bus session
 bus creation.
